<TITLE> Pakistan begins military offensive against militants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ISLAMABAD, April 26 (bdnews24.com/ Reuters) - Pakistani security forces on Sunday began an offensive to stop the Taliban's creeping advances in a troubled northwestern region, the military said. A military spokesman said scores of militants, including a commander, and a soldier were killed in the operation in Lower Dir district in the North West Frontier Province. "Intense exchange of fire is going on in Lower Dir," he told Reuters.
